{"title_page": "Bricostore", "text_new": "{{Infobox company |\n name = Bricostore |\n logo = [[Image:Bricostore.png|250px|BricoStore Logo]]|\n image= [[Image:Bricostore Ploie\u0219ti.jpg|250px|Bricostore]]|\n type = [[Private company|Private]]|\n foundation = 1991 ([[Paris]])|\n location = Paris, [[France]]|\n key_people = Philippe Bresson, CEO & Chairman|\n industry = [[Retailer|Retail]]|\n products = [[Home improvement]] [[tool]]s, [[gardening|garden supplies & plants]]|\n homepage = [http://www.bricostore.com/ www.bricostore.com]|\n}}\n\n'''Bricostore''' was a [[France|French]] [[home improvement]] [[retailer]] which operated stores in [[France]], [[Hungary]], [[Romania]] and [[Croatia]]. Founded by the French Bresson family in [[Paris]] in 1991, the company operated 7 stores in France until 2001, when they sold 6 stores to [[Bricorama]] and closed the remaining one.<ref>{{Cite web| url=https://www.lsa-conso.fr/bricorama-rachete-l-enseigne-bricostore,286 |title=Bricorama rach\u00e8te l'enseigne Bricostore |publisher=lsa-conso.fr |date=4 January 2001}}</ref>\n\nIn Hungary, Bricostore opened its first store in 1999 and had a total of 9 stores. The stores were closed in 2012 and subsequently sold to other retailers and companies, such as [[OBI]] who bought 3 stores.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://trademagazin.hu/en/a-bricostore-a-gazdasagi-valsaggal-indokolja-a-kivonulast-magyarorszagrol/ |title=The Bricostore justifies the withdrawal from Hungary with the economic crisis |publisher=trademagazin.hu |date= 19 November 2012}}</ref>\n\nBricostore opened the first store in Romania in March 2002 and reached 15 stores in March 2011. In April 2013, the British [[Kingfisher]] bought the stores for 75 million euro and rebranded them as [[Brico D\u00e9p\u00f4t]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.capital.ro/detalii-articole/stiri/kingfisher-va-plati-75-milioane-de-euro-pentru-cele-15-magazine-bricostore-180903.html |title=Kingfisher va pl\u0103ti 75 milioane de euro pentru cele 15 magazine Bricostore |publisher=capital.ro |date=18 April 2013}}</ref>\n\nBricostore in Croatia was opened in 2004 and later was opened another 2 stores. The stores were closed in 2013.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://seenews.com/news/diy-retailer-bricostore-to-exit-croatian-market-352692 |title=The Bricostore justifies the withdrawal from Hungary with the economic crisis |publisher=seenews.com |date= 13 May 2013}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/*/http://www.bricostore.hu/ Bricostore Hungary] (archive)\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/*/http://www.bricostore.ro/ Bricostore Romania] (archive)\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/*/http://www.bricostore.hr/ Bricostore Croatia] (archive)\n\n[[Category:Retail companies established in 1991]]\n[[Category:Hardware stores]]\n[[Category:Retail companies of France]]\n[[Category:Defunct companies of France]]\n[[Category:Defunct retail companies of Romania]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company |\n name = Bricostore |\n logo = [[Image:Bricostore.png|250px|BricoStore Logo]]|\n image= [[Image:Bricostore Ploie\u0219ti.jpg|250px|Bricostore]]|\n type = [[Private company|Private]]|\n foundation = 1991 ([[Paris]])|\n location = Paris, [[France]]|\n key_people = Philippe Bresson, CEO & Chairman|\n industry = [[Retailer|Retail]]|\n products = [[Home improvement]] [[tool]]s <br/> [[gardening|garden supplies & plants]]|\n homepage = [http://www.bricostore.com/ www.bricostore.com]|\n}}\n\n'''Bricostore''' was a [[France|French]] [[home improvement]] [[retailer]] which operated stores in [[France]], [[Hungary]], [[Romania]] and [[Croatia]]. Founded by the French Bresson family in [[Paris]] in 1991, the company operated 7 stores in France until 2001, when they sold 6 stores to [[Bricorama]] and closed the remaining one.<ref>{{Cite web| url=https://www.lsa-conso.fr/bricorama-rachete-l-enseigne-bricostore,286 |title=Bricorama rach\u00e8te l'enseigne Bricostore |publisher=lsa-conso.fr |date=4 January 2001}}</ref>\n\nIn Hungary, Bricostore opened its first store in 1999 and had a total of 9 stores. The stores were closed in 2012 and subsequently sold to other retailers and companies, such as [[OBI]] who bought 3 stores.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://trademagazin.hu/en/a-bricostore-a-gazdasagi-valsaggal-indokolja-a-kivonulast-magyarorszagrol/ |title=The Bricostore justifies the withdrawal from Hungary with the economic crisis |publisher=trademagazin.hu |date= 19 November 2012}}</ref>\n\nBricostore opened the first store in Romania in March 2002 and reached 15 stores in March 2011. In April 2013, the British [[Kingfisher]] bought the stores for 75 million euro and rebranded them as [[Brico D\u00e9p\u00f4t]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.capital.ro/detalii-articole/stiri/kingfisher-va-plati-75-milioane-de-euro-pentru-cele-15-magazine-bricostore-180903.html |title=Kingfisher va pl\u0103ti 75 milioane de euro pentru cele 15 magazine Bricostore |publisher=capital.ro |date=18 April 2013}}</ref>\n\nBricostore in Croatia was opened in 2004 and later was opened another 2 stores. The stores were closed in 2013.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://seenews.com/news/diy-retailer-bricostore-to-exit-croatian-market-352692 |title=The Bricostore justifies the withdrawal from Hungary with the economic crisis |publisher=seenews.com |date= 13 May 2013}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/*/http://www.bricostore.hu/ Bricostore Hungary] (archive)\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/*/http://www.bricostore.ro/ Bricostore Romania] (archive)\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/*/http://www.bricostore.hr/ Bricostore Croatia] (archive)\n\n[[Category:Retail companies established in 1991]]\n[[Category:Hardware stores]]\n[[Category:Retail companies of France]]\n[[Category:Defunct companies of France]]\n[[Category:Defunct retail companies of Romania]]\n", "name_user": "Daniel.9", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bricostore"}
